dct_description_sm: Published according to Act of Parliament at the Hydrographic Office of the Admiralty May 6th, 1854 ; Engraved by J. & C. Walker ; Sold by J.D. Potter Agent for the Admiralty Charts.
Depths shown by soundings, relief by hachures.
Approximate magnetic variation in 1916, increasing about 9' annually.
Shows low water areas, coasts, towns and villages, currents, lights, monasteries, Novo Dvina Fort.
